[[<]]
Some time later, Buddy decided to make its way back into the interconnected structure. Returning to the workshop, the commotion had not subsided, with different machines being serviced and different beings doing the servicing. Approaching a different worker, a pale, shorter human with semi-translucent skin, Buddy introduced itself in the only way it really knew how.

//"Hello, I am Buddy.aic. I come on behalf of the Foundation and Humanity."//

The humanoid stopped and set down the large canister he was holding, looking at Buddy with a perplexed expression.

"Huh—?"

Suddenly, he staggered, clutching his head. Soon after, the others in the room all started to sway and express distress in a similar fashion, although it was not clear why. They fell to the ground in moaning heaps, eyes rolling back into their heads. Unbeknownst to the drone, this was currently happening to every sapient lifeform with a brain on the Stack. Buddy would not understand the full scope of the event, for it lacked an organic consciousness and, as previously stated, was a cold and unfeeling machine.

As the beings writhed in agony, they spoke, sometimes one at a time, sometimes in groups. Their words called out like the beckon of a worried mother, fueled by an agency that implied true, unyielding suffering.

The stream of words and random voices pieced together to form a single thread of raw consciousness, one that reached out to speak through those whose minds could feel its contact.

Thus, Buddy was the only one who actually heard the message. It echoed like a fragmented broadcast rearranged into sentences as beings around the Stack rendered their will unknowingly.


